                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">Fol. 1va</locus>: Excerpt from the First Epistle of John (1 John 1:1-7).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 1va: መልእክተ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ሐዋርያ፡ ወልደ፡ ዘብዴዎስ፡ ቀዳማዊ፡ ንዜንወክሙ፡ በእንተ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The text is the first reading material for students in reading school.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#133ra">Fol. 133ra</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 133ra: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘዓፀደ፡ ወይን፡ ዓቅበ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘሚካኤል፡ በኃይለ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ውሉዶሙ፡ ዘአጽሐ[ፍ]ዋ፡ ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ። ወቄሰ፡ ገበዙሂ፡ ቄስ፡ ተክሌ፡ ወአቡሁ፡ አተወ፡ ብርሃን፡ ኢትርሥዑኒ፡ ፩አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን።  </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is somewhat difficult to understand. It mentions ʿAḍädä Wäyn, ʿAqbä Mikaʾel, Zä-Mikaʾel (and) their children (?; wǝludomu) and Bä-Ḫaylä ʾIyäsus as commissioners, in the time of qesä gäbäz Täkle.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#133ra">Fol. 133ra</locus>-vb: “Blessing Prayer” from the Anaphora of the Apostles. <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 133ra-vb: ጸሎተ፡ ቡራኬ፡ ኦሥሉስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ባርክ፡ ዲበ፡ ሕዝብከ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Anaphora of the Apostles: from verse 10-21.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Immediate corrections marked by thin lines above and below the word: fol. 9rb.&#xD;
- Minor notes: fols. 2r, 26r.</item>
